        "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3394-9805" ;
    dc:date "2025-12-03"^^xsd:string ;
    ns3:providedBy "http://informatics.jax.org"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:comment "Motor nerve conduction velocity was found significantly reduced in sciatic nerve from P1c-deficient as well as from conditional knock-out mice."^^xsd:string,
        "Neural Plectin Isoform (Plectin 1c)"^^xsd:string,
        "Using isoform-specific antibodies, we found P1c to be expressed late in development and to associate with postsynaptic dendrites of central nervous system neurons, motorneurons of spinal cord, sciatic nerve axons, and Schwann cells."^^xsd:string .

